'''= What we share. Creations of both nature and society that belong to all of us equally, and should be maintained for future generations.''' The Commons has the potential to replace the commodity as the determining form of re-/producing societal living conditions. Such a replacement can only occur, if communities constitute themselves for every aspect of life, in order to take "their" commons back and to reintegrate them into a new need-focused logic of re-/production. [http://www.onthecommons.org/content.php?id=2651]

